<br>
To go back on topic, then, yeah, the rpmarket is a nice idea in theory, and it kinda worked for a couple of weeks, but this was a looooong time ago.  Once the bazaar worked correctly, a huge chunk of roleplay reality jumped out of the window of a 40 story building.  One could not forbid a race, followers of an opposing god, and so forth from buying the gear they earned.<br>
<br>
